Arcadia
=======

Lightweight Linux distribution based on minimalism.

Requirements
------------

- C toolchain targeting $ARCH-linux-musl with static libc
- Gzip or Pigz
- POSIX sh
- Prometheus
- UNIX tools

Bootstrappable requirements
---------------------------

Some extra dependencies are needed to build packages, but they can easily be
retrieved with Prometheus by installing them to a temporary directory and
updating the PATH

	# prometheus -is . -p tmpdir tmp/*
	# export PATH="tmpdir:$PATH"

Installation
------------

The ARCH environment variable specifies the architecture of the target. If it
is not set, it defaults to the architecture of the build machine.

	# export ARCH=target-arch

If needed, it is possible to specify all the common variables of the cross
toolchain, such as CC, AR, etc.

	# export CC=cross-cc

It is assumed that the root and EFI partitions of the new system are mounted to
/mnt and /mnt/boot respectively and that the current directory is this
repository.
